Fix Lua 5.5 incompatibility in ltcn's tokenset_to_list()

Lua 5.5 makes the control variable of a generic `for ... in` loop read-only
(implicitly <const>), and ltcn's `tokenset_to_list` assigns to it:

    ./ltcn.lua:61: attempt to assign to const variable 's'

Assigning to a const is a *compile-time* error, so this is not confined to the
error-reporting path that tokenset_to_list serves: the chunk never compiles and
`require("ltcn")` itself fails. ltcn is entirely unusable on Lua 5.5. Every
TabuLua table-parsing test hits this: 22 failures on Lua 5.5.0, while Lua 5.1
through 5.4 are unaffected.

ltcn's own test suite reproduces it: stock `make check` dies on its first test.

The fix copies the loop variable into a fresh local before rewriting it. It is
behaviour-preserving (verified on Lua 5.4: identical sorted token list for the
same input set, quoting of `'` included) and valid on Lua 5.1-5.5.

Applies to ltcn master (https://gitlab.com/craigbarnes/ltcn), commit abde2ef8
(2024-11-04) — which is also what `luarocks install --server=https://luarocks.org/dev
ltcn` installs as scm-1. Upstream has had no commit since 2024-11-04 and its issue
tracker and merge-request list are both empty, so Docker/Dockerfile.lua55 applies this
to the installed rock in place. If the patch ever fails to apply, upstream has moved:
re-check the tracker before regenerating. See TODO/lua55_compatibility.md.

--- a/ltcn.lua
+++ b/ltcn.lua
@@ -56,11 +56,12 @@
     local list, i = {}, 0
     for s in pairs(set) do
         i = i + 1
-        if s:match("^%p$") then
+        local token = s
+        if token:match("^%p$") then
             -- Quote punctuation characters
-            s = (s == "'") and '"\'"' or ("'" .. s .. "'")
+            token = (token == "'") and '"\'"' or ("'" .. token .. "'")
         end
-        list[i] = s
+        list[i] = token
     end
     sort(list)
     return list
